    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-09-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-09-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="195"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d195">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Dayton to Mr. Seward</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 535.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-09-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 9, 1864.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: As the most satisfactory mode of apprising the
                    foreign department here of your action in the case of Mr. Mansfield, our consul
                    at Tabasco, I read your despatch No. 618 to Mr. Drouyn de l’Huys. He seemed much
                    gratified with the kind and courteous manner in which you expressed yourself in
                    relation to his communication of the information he had received in relation to
                    the character and habits of our consul at that post.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WM. L. DAYTON.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,
                            &amp;c., &amp;c.,</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
